{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1278,"text":"So, as researchers, something\nthat we often do is use immense resources"},{"time":5523,"text":"to achieve certain capabilities,\nor achieve certain goals."},{"time":8826,"text":"And this is essential\nto the progress of science,"},{"time":11385,"text":"or exploration of what is possible."},{"time":13734,"text":"But it creates this unfortunate situation"},{"time":15766,"text":"where a tiny, tiny fraction of the world"},{"time":17806,"text":"can actually participate\nin this exploration"},{"time":19926,"text":"or can benefit from that technology."},{"time":21771,"text":"Something that motivates me,"},{"time":23200,"text":"and gets me really excited\nabout my research,"},{"time":25437,"text":"is when I see simple opportunities"},{"time":27167,"text":"to drastically change that distribution\nand make the technology accessible"},{"time":30991,"text":"to a much wider percentage\nof the population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33124,"text":"I'm going to show you two videos\nthat have gotten a lot of attention"},{"time":36680,"text":"that I think embody this philosophy."},{"time":38474,"text":"And they actually use\nthe Nintendo Wii Remote."},{"time":40931,"text":"For those of you who aren't\nfamiliar with this device,"},{"time":43496,"text":"it's a $40 video game controller."},{"time":46217,"text":"And it's mostly advertised\nfor its motion-sensing capabilities:"},{"time":49386,"text":"so you can swing a tennis racket,\nor hit a baseball bat."},{"time":52052,"text":"But what actually interests me a lot more"},{"time":54434,"text":"is the fact that in the tip\nof each controller"},{"time":56616,"text":"is a relatively high-performing\ninfrared camera."},{"time":59430,"text":"And I'm going to show you\ntwo demos of why this is useful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63913,"text":"So here, I have my computer\nset up with the projector,"},{"time":66841,"text":"and I have a Wii Remote\nsitting on top of it."},{"time":69222,"text":"And, for example, if you're in a school\nthat doesn't have a lot money,"},{"time":73104,"text":"probably a lot of schools,"},{"time":74555,"text":"or if you're in an office environment,\nand you want an interactive whiteboard,"},{"time":78261,"text":"normally these cost\nabout two to three thousand dollars."},{"time":80935,"text":"So I'm going to show you\nhow to create one with a Wii Remote."},{"time":85067,"text":"Now, this requires\nanother piece of hardware,"},{"time":88675,"text":"which is this infrared pen."},{"time":90267,"text":"You can probably make\nthis yourself for about five dollars"},{"time":93101,"text":"with a quick trip to the Radio Shack."},{"time":94957,"text":"It's got a battery,\na button and an infrared LED --"},{"time":97539,"text":"you guys can't see it --"},{"time":98721,"text":"but it turns on\nwhenever I push the button."},{"time":100976,"text":"Now, what this means is\nthat if I run this piece of software,"},{"time":105538,"text":"the camera sees the infrared dot,"},{"time":109975,"text":"and I can register the location\nof the camera pixels"},{"time":114184,"text":"to the projector pixels."},{"time":115351,"text":"And now this is like\nan interactive whiteboard surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118057,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":119803,"text":"So for about $50 of hardware,\nyou can have your own whiteboard."},{"time":123716,"text":"This is Adobe Photoshop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125923,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":131612,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132692,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134349,"text":"The software for this\nI've actually put on my website"},{"time":136984,"text":"and have let people download it for free."},{"time":139015,"text":"In the three months\nthis project has been public,"},{"time":141410,"text":"it's been downloaded\nover half a million times."},{"time":143702,"text":"So teachers and students\nall around the world"},{"time":145967,"text":"are already using this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147337,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":152760,"text":"Although it does do it for 50 dollars,"},{"time":155077,"text":"there are some limitations\nof this approach."},{"time":157158,"text":"You get about 80 percent of the way there,\nfor one percent of the cost."},{"time":160584,"text":"Another nice thing is that a camera\ncan see multiple dots,"},{"time":163386,"text":"so this is actually a multi-touch,\ninteractive whiteboard system as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166873,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":169095,"text":"For the second demo,"},{"time":170247,"text":"I have this Wii Remote\nthat's actually next to the TV."},{"time":172895,"text":"So it's pointing away from the display,\nrather than pointing at the display."},{"time":177119,"text":"And why this is interesting"},{"time":179406,"text":"is that if you put on, say,\na pair of safety glasses,"},{"time":183144,"text":"that have two infrared dots in them,"},{"time":184982,"text":"they are going to give the computer\nan approximation of your head location."},{"time":190259,"text":"And why this is interesting"},{"time":191585,"text":"is I have this sort of application\nrunning on the computer monitor,"},{"time":194752,"text":"which has a 3D room,\nwith some targets floating in it."},{"time":197308,"text":"And you can see that it\nlooks like a 3D room."},{"time":199571,"text":"kind of like a video game,\nit sort of looks 3D,"},{"time":202942,"text":"but for the most part,\nthe image looks pretty flat,"},{"time":205433,"text":"and bound to the surface of the screen."},{"time":207315,"text":"But if we turn on head tracking --"},{"time":212720,"text":"the computer can change\nthe image that's on the screen"},{"time":215529,"text":"and make it respond to the head movements."},{"time":217569,"text":"So let's switch back to that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218974,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":232645,"text":"So this has actually\nbeen a little bit startling"},{"time":235888,"text":"to the game-development community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237546,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":239392,"text":"Because this is about 10 dollars\nof additional hardware"},{"time":242272,"text":"if you already have a Nintendo Wii."},{"time":244155,"text":"So I'm looking forward\nto seeing some games,"},{"time":246464,"text":"and actually Louis Castle,\nthat's him down there,"},{"time":248983,"text":"last week announced that Electronic Arts,\none of the largest game publishers,"},{"time":252646,"text":"is releasing a game in May\nthat has a little Easter egg feature"},{"time":255671,"text":"for supporting this type of head tracking."},{"time":257988,"text":"And that's from less than five months"},{"time":259938,"text":"from a prototype in my lab\nto a major commercial product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263088,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268605,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269858,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272121,"text":"But actually, to me,\nwhat's almost more interesting"},{"time":274544,"text":"than either of these two projects"},{"time":276140,"text":"is how people actually\nfound out about them."},{"time":278459,"text":"YouTube has really changed the way,\nor changed the speed,"},{"time":282023,"text":"in which a single individual"},{"time":283381,"text":"can actually spread\nan idea around the world."},{"time":285632,"text":"I'm doing some research\nin my lab with a video camera,"},{"time":288656,"text":"and within the first week,\na million people had seen this work,"},{"time":291633,"text":"and literally within days,\nengineers, teachers and students"},{"time":295248,"text":"from around the world were already\nposting their own YouTube videos"},{"time":298463,"text":"of them using my system\nor derivatives of this work."},{"time":301847,"text":"So I hope to see more\nof that in the future,"},{"time":304411,"text":"and hope online video distribution\nto be embraced by the research community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308007,"text":"So thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309284,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}